&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting time for the Buckinghamshire Integrated Care Partnership as we work together to improve the health and well being of the population. This role supports the Strategy and ICT team to implement an exciting new vision for Trust working in partnership with GPs, local authorities and our patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is a varied role with the opportunity to support a growing digital agenda that will transform the way patients access our services and our colleagues provide care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a great opportunity for someone interested in working with a variety of partners in a fast moving environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The key responsibilities include diary management for David Williams, Director of Strategy and Business Development as well as providing administrative support to his deputy, Dan Leveson. Organising a range of meetings and workshops with internal members of staff and external stakeholders, such as Buckinghamshire Council, CCG and other health care providers with the timely co-ordination of agendas, papers and minutes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;David Williams, Director of Strategy &amp; Business Development&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address : david.williams26@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
